<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06283235 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06283235 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  Scare us -- if you can.;   Halloween is coming, and we want to be frightenedby kids. We also want all of our readers to be frightened by kids. We arelooking for scary stories and original artwork by kids in grades one throughsix.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  East Extra  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  KIDS! WE WANT HALLOWEEN HORRORS  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Also ran in EX4/1, WL1  </MEMO><TEXT>     Ghosts, monsters, bats and vampires, shadows on the walls and noises in thenight will do -- or anything else that you think will make us yell, &quot;Yeeek!&quot;;  Write or draw it by the light of the moon if you want. Have some of yourfriends or classmates do the same.;   Send it to us by werewolf or headlesshorseman or by the U.S. Postal Service.;   But in any case, get it to us bynoon Oct. 21. That is your &quot;deadline.&quot;;   Please try to limit your stories totwo pages, typed or neatly written. Include your name, age, grade, school andyour address and phone number. Make sure the story or art is your own -- no&quot;ghost&quot; writers please. Also, only one entry per author.;   Address the creepytales and art to Scary Stuff, San Jose Mercury News, 750 Ridder Park Drive,San Jose 95190. We will print the most fearsome, and excerpts from others,Oct. 30.  </TEXT><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911009  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  October  </MONTH><PG.COL>  1  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  206  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday, October 9, 199100283235,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>